Basil, coriander, makrut lime leaves and green chillies give Thai Green its signature colour, as well as its fragrant flavour. Our Thai Green Style Double Chicken Curry only takes 10 minutes to prep for an easy dinner that gives you time back!

== Jasmine Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Mushrooms ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{80%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until slightly browned, ~{3-4%mins}.

Meanwhile, cut the @Lime{1} into wedges.

== Curry ==

Once the mushrooms have browned, stir in the @Diced British Chicken Breast{480%g}, @Coconut Milk{180%ml}, @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Thai Green Style Paste{45%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the curry's ready, squeeze in half the lime juice from the lime wedges.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and share between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over your Thai green style chicken curry.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!